content:
Deleting a Category Group

Deleting a category group deletes all of its categories and removes all associations between the categories and articles or questions.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Data categories are available in all editions with Knowledge except Professional Edition. 

To delete a category group:
From Setup, enter Data Category in the Quick Find box, then select Data Category Setup.
Hover your cursor over the category group name.
Click the Delete Category Group icon ().
Select the checkbox in the confirmation dialog, then click OK.

When deleted, a category group moves to the Deleted Category Groups section, which holds items for 15 days before they are permanently erased and cannot be recovered. During this time, you can restore or permanently erase it immediately.

Deleting a category group also:
Deletes all categories within that group.
Removes all associations between the group's categories and articles or questions.
Removes all associations between the group's categories and visibility.
As applicable, removes the category drop-down menu from the Articles tab in all channels, the Article Management tab, and your company's public knowledge base.
title: Deleting Data Category Groups
